We recommend that the Municipal Treasurer, initiate the conduct of physical inventory taking of all properties of the municipal government and prepare and submit the corresponding RPCPPE to the audit team as basis to determine the existence, accuracy and validity of reported balance in the financial statements. Also, management to establish internal control policies and procedures over Property and Supply Management system to:
a. Safeguard the accuracy and reliability of the information by preventing and detecting errors;
b. Prevent or detect loss of assets and records on a timely basis;
c. Protect against waste in all aspects of operation and discourage other types of inefficient use of resources; and
d. Provide reasonable assurance that those procedures and rules are adhered to by the agency personnel.
